  						<table border='0' cellpadding='3' cellspacing='0' width='92%'>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%' bgcolor='#0E024D' class='spti2' align='center'><B> WEREWOLF KILLERS ON THE LOOSE </B></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><font face='verdana' size='2pt'>

         <p>   A gentle wind blew on the plains of West Karana, stirring up the
short waving grass and giving the lush green field an appearance of ocean
waves. Sabereye closed his eyes and took in a deep breath of clean air and
dreamed of his return to Halas the next morn. It had been nearly four
seasons since his last visit and his barbarian brothers would soon start to
worry if he did not return.  </p>

<p> "Hey Saber, wake up man! We've got a mission to accomplish," Lyrre said. </p>

<p> "Yea, you Barbarians are always staring off into space and talking about the
tribunal and your precious doggies!" Kaalas joking relayed to Sabereye. </p>

        <p>   Lyrre and Kaalas, two of Sabereye's most trusted party members
and friends. How he came to be with these two men he will never know. Lyrre,
a half-elf Bard, had watched Sabereye grow up and had tutored him well in
the art of war and combat. His bright blue armor shined and showed the pride
that he put into his appearance. He kept fidgeting with his Yak's, hoping
graciously to start the carnage and sing songs of glorious battle.
Sabereye turned to glance upon his lifelong friend Kaalas. A human, who had
decided to follow the ways of Tunare and become a druid, Kaalas was always
there to help Sabereye out of trouble and to travel wherever the winds would
take him. This small group of travelers had faired well together.
</p>
<p>"Look, there he is," Kaalas said, "the Werewolf hunter himself." I have
heard tell that he is an easy opponent. I don't think that we should have
any problems at all taking him down." </p>

<p>"You sure about this?" Sabereye said, "I can remember many times that things
have looked easy and I have ended up dead!" Sabereye begins to laugh
heartily and pulls out a flask, taking a mighty swig of Honey Mead. </p>

<p>"Well, you were probably drunk most of that time you foul Shaman!" Kaalas
prodded.</p>

<p>A light began to shine on the horizon and as both Kaalas and Sabereye looked
up, they saw Lyrre come running back to them.</p>

<p>"He's there all right, and he doesn't seem to be too bad. We should be able
to take him with just the three of us." Lyrre said.</p>

<p>"Ok, here's the plan: Sabereye, you sic your dog 'Fluffy' on him and then
lower his resistance to our magic. Then proceed to disease and nuke him as
you see fit. I will snare him and bring down the fires of heaven. Lyrre, you
do what you do best, slice and dice. With all that in place, we should be
having dinner at Harpy's Tavern by midday."</p>

<p> Sabereye bends down to gently stroke Fluffy's fur and coo her. Fluffy looks
up at her master with loving eyes and gently nudges his hand. Reaching into
his potion bag, Sabereye brings out a small biscuit and feeds it to his
loving pet. Lyrre looks over his comrades and calmly states: </p>

<p>"It's Go Time!"</p>

      <p>  Lyrre rushes in with a battle roar that would scare a Hill giant.
That is when the trouble began. Sabereye and Kaalas began to cast their
spells when suddenly the whole world went dark. Sabereye could not see, but
he could hear his poor pet screaming in pain.</p>

<p>"What's going on!" Saber shouts.</p>

<p>"He's blinding and fearing us!" Kaalas yells. "Your dog is getting the beat
down of its life!"</p>

     <p>   Suddenly, the light comes back, and Saber turns to see his pet dead
and Lyrre feverishly whacking away at this madman. He turns to run and aid
his friend, when bright shining skulls begin to engulf him. He loses control
of his movement and begins to run in the opposite direction. Then the world
goes dark again. How could this be happening? This was supposed to be easy.</p>

<p>"Saber, watch yourself!" Kaalas shouted, " You're bleeding like a stuck
orc!".</p>

      <p>  Truly, Sabereye was feeling weak. The world was starting to grow
small and faint, and soon, he fell to the ground with a sickening thud. All
that Saber could do was lay there on this lush green ground and watch his
friend's battle to the death. He then found himself rather naked and
bitterly cold near a sign that said "To Qeynos Hills".</p>

<p>"Lyrre? Kaalas? Are you guys ok!!"</p>

<p>"Hehe, yea....I evaced out, but cound not get you both close enough together. Lyrre buddy, are you among the living?" Kaalas
said.</p>

<p>"Yep, thank the maker for Selo's! Saber, where are you at...I'll drag your
body to you."</p>

     <p>   Sabereye sat down and consented Lyrre to the dragging of his corpse.
Deep down inside, he knew that this would not be the last time he would hear
that comment again. </p>
 </font></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
	  <td width='100%'><small>By <b>Sabereye</b> Submited on 3/7/2001</small></td>
